<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-11T15:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-11T15:36:00-05:00" n="795" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d795">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6765.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-11T14:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1913—2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have been notified informally by Díaz that if he is successful in the
                            battle today, he will expect that the United States will immediately
                            recognize his belligerency.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>